.\pipeline\chain-state\publicmenu-260320-171535-codex-findings.md:5:1. [P0] Polling timer leak survives unmount in `useTableSession` — `scheduleNext()` in [useTableSession.jsx](/C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/base/useTableSession.jsx#L670) always registers the next `setTimeout` even after cleanup has set `cancelled=true`. If `pollSessionData()` is still in flight during unmount, the callback at lines 671-674 can create a fresh orphan timer and continue polling a stale component. FIX: guard `scheduleNext()` with `if (cancelled) return` before `setTimeout`, and reschedule only after the current poll finishes and confirms the effect is still active.
