.\pipeline\chain-state\publicmenu-260321-093745-codex-findings.md:6:2. [P1] Hall confirmation shows raw cart total, not real order total - Hall orders are persisted with `total_amount: finalTotal` (`pages/PublicMenu/base/x.jsx:2420`), but the confirmation screen is fed `cart.reduce(...)` (`pages/PublicMenu/base/x.jsx:2540-2559`). Any loyalty discount or redeemed points makes the guest-facing total wrong. FIX: pass `finalTotal` or the created order's stored `total_amount` into the hall confirmation payload.
.\pipeline\chain-state\publicmenu-260321-093745-codex-findings.md:9:5. [P1] Visit-state UI is still count-driven instead of state-driven - `CartView` always renders the same section stack when data exists (`pages/PublicMenu/base/CartView.jsx:557-780`, `pages/PublicMenu/base/CartView.jsx:783-1277`), and the sticky footer exists only when `cart.length > 0` (`pages/PublicMenu/base/CartView.jsx:1245-1277`). In `x.jsx`, `hallStickyMode` has only `cart`, `myBill`, `tableOrders`, `cartEmpty` and is derived from counts (`pages/PublicMenu/base/x.jsx:2056-2115`). This misses the required visit/draft matrix: no bottom CTA for sent-orders-without-draft, no unpaid secondary line for new-draft-after-send, no paid/closed fade-out behavior. `useTableSession` also merges draft into table total and never filters paid orders (`pages/PublicMenu/base/useTableSession.jsx:722-747`, `pages/PublicMenu/base/useTableSession.jsx:784-788`). FIX: derive explicit visit state from session/order/payment status, compute unpaid sent totals separately from draft totals, and render drawer/sticky CTAs from that state matrix instead of `cart.length` or order counts.
