.\pipeline\chain-state\publicmenu-260321-195108-comparison.md:46:### 8. [P2→SKIP] `useTableSession` loses restored guests with only `_id` — OUT OF SCOPE
.\pipeline\chain-state\publicmenu-260321-195108-comparison.md:74:- Codex #5: useTableSession guest _id normalization (new bug)
.\pipeline\chain-state\publicmenu-260321-195108-codex-findings.md:9:5. [P2] `useTableSession` loses restored guests that only have `_id` — The hook correctly defines `normalizeGuestId()`, but later syncs `currentGuestIdRef.current = currentGuest?.id || null` in `pages/PublicMenu/base/useTableSession.jsx`. If a restored `SessionGuest` only carries `_id`, the ref is reset to `null`, so polling keeps re-running guest restore and downstream logic can behave as if no current guest exists. FIX: store `normalizeGuestId(currentGuest)` in the ref, and align any other guest-id reads in this file with the same normalization rule.
.\pipeline\chain-state\publicmenu-260321-173133-codex-findings.md:8:4. [P1] Session restore stops forever after a single transient failure - `useTableSession.jsx:265-487` sets `didAttemptRestoreRef.current = true` before the async restore work, then swallows all errors in the outer `catch` without resetting it. If any restore request fails once, the effect never retries until the table changes or the page is reloaded. FIX: reset the attempt flag on failure, or only mark restore as attempted after successful completion and add retry/backoff handling for recoverable errors.
.\pipeline\chain-state\publicmenu-260321-140331-codex-findings.md:8:5. [P1] `x.jsx` is not wired to the sibling `base/*.jsx` modules being reviewed — it imports `MenuView`, `CartView`, `ModeTabs`, `CheckoutView`, and `useTableSession` from `@/components/publicMenu/...` and `refactor/...`, not from `pages/PublicMenu/base/*` ([x.jsx](/C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/base/x.jsx#L100)). That means fixes made to the scoped base files can miss runtime behavior entirely, including the PM-062/PM-064 paths called out in the task context. FIX: either switch `x.jsx` to import the sibling base modules or stop treating these base files as the active implementation.
.\pipeline\chain-state\publicmenu-260321-140331-cc-findings.md:40:15. **[P2] Bottom Sheet Drawer uses x.jsx's `isVerifyingCode` and `codeVerificationError` but these come from useTableSession hook** (x.jsx:1512,1516) — These are already in x.jsx scope from the hook destructuring, so they work. But the Bottom Sheet lacks the auto-verify trigger that would SET `isVerifyingCode` — verifyTableCode is never called from the Bottom Sheet. FIX: Add auto-verify effect in x.jsx Bottom Sheet scope, or add the CTA button that calls verifyTableCode.
.\pipeline\chain-state\publicmenu-260321-132753-codex-findings.md:9:5. [P1] Hall session restore never retries after a transient error — `useTableSession.jsx` sets `didAttemptRestoreRef.current = true` before async restore work and never resets it on failure. One temporary read error leaves `tableSession` unset, polling never starts, and the hall visit stays empty until refresh. FIX: reset the guard on failure or replace it with bounded retry/backoff plus a visible restore error state.
.\pipeline\chain-state\publicmenu-260321-132753-codex-findings.md:10:6. [P2] Bill and table totals use raw values in arithmetic — `useTableSession.jsx` accumulates `item.line_total` and `o.total_amount` without numeric coercion in split-bill and `tableTotal` calculations. If Base44 returns numeric strings, totals concatenate instead of sum. FIX: wrap every accumulated monetary field in `Number(...) || 0` before adding.
.\pipeline\chain-state\publicmenu-260321-093745-comparison.md:12:- **Fix consensus:** Use `finalTotal` or stored `total_amount` for the confirmation display.
.\pages\PublicMenu\cartview-260415-105013-e600-codex-findings.md:5:1. [P0] `getOrderStatus` drops `internal_code` — `pages/PublicMenu/useTableSession.jsx:797-811` resolves `stage_id` through `stagesMap`, but it only returns `{ icon, label, color }`. That leaves `CartView` without a stable signal for terminal `OrderStages.internal_code === 'finish'`, so Fix 1 cannot be implemented stage-first. FIX: return `internal_code: stage.internal_code || null` for mapped stages and `internal_code: null` in the fallback object.
.\pages\PublicMenu\cartview-260415-092055-289b-codex-findings.md:5:1. [P0] `statusBuckets` still groups by legacy `o.status` only — In [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:427), the drawer decides `served` vs `in_progress` from `o.status`, while terminal completion now comes from `Order.stage_id -> OrderStages.internal_code`. A waiter/SOM move to the `finish` stage can therefore leave the order in `В работе`, which matches the bug described in Fix 1. `getOrderStatus` in [useTableSession.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/useTableSession.jsx:797) also still returns only `{ icon, label, color }`, so CartView has no stage code to consume. FIX: extend `getOrderStatus(order)` to return `internal_code`, then make `statusBuckets` stage-first with legacy `o.status` fallback exactly as described in Fix 1.
