.\pages\StaffOrdersMobile\staffordersmobile-260415-225055-2937-codex-findings.md:8:4. [P1] Fix A ground truth is missing — the RELEASE file has no `openSessions` query or `openSessionByTableId` map near the query block (`3513-3526`), no `openSessionId` field in the table-group builder (`3740-3789`), and no TableSession override in `filteredGroups` / `tabCounts` (`3832-3871`). The page still decides Active vs Completed only from orders and requests, so one stale signal can keep a closed table in Active, and a table with no visible orders/requests can disappear instead of being forced into Completed. FIX: add a `useQuery` for open `TableSession` rows, derive `openSessionByTableId`, attach `openSessionId` to table groups, and short-circuit table groups in `filteredGroups` and `tabCounts` to Completed when no open session exists.
.\pages\StaffOrdersMobile\staffordersmobile-260415-225055-2937-codex-findings.md:9:5. [P1] Fix A cache refresh is missing in `confirmCloseTable` — `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/260415-00 StaffOrdersMobile RELEASE.jsx:4146-4155` refreshes orders and service requests only. Once the TableSession ground truth is added, this handler will still leave the tab classification stale until a later refresh unless it explicitly invalidates the new `openSessions` query. FIX: add `queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ["openSessions"] })` immediately after `closeSession(sessionId, tableId)` alongside the existing refresh path.
.\pages\StaffOrdersMobile\staffordersmobile-260415-161942-d5a3-codex-findings.md:6:2. [P1] Close-table flow still leaves request state active — `components/sessionHelpers.js:158-169` closes the `TableSession` and orders only; it never completes open `ServiceRequest` rows for the table. Then `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/260414-02 StaffOrdersMobile RELEASE.jsx:4148-4152` refetches only orders, so `activeRequests` can continue to satisfy `hasActiveRequest` in `filteredGroups` and keep the table out of "Completed" until a later poll. FIX: after closing the session orders, also close open `ServiceRequest`s for that table, and refetch or invalidate `["serviceRequests"]` after `closeSession(sessionId)` for non-kitchen users.
