.\pages\PublicMenu\review_2026-04-07.md:4:1. [P1] Fix 1 not implemented in `processHallOrder` — [`pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx`](C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx) lines 3709-3747 still call `getNextOrderNumber(partner, 'hall')` once, create one `Order` with `total_amount: finalTotal`, then `bulkCreate` all cart lines under that single `order.id`. That preserves the old `1 Order + N OrderItems` model, so StaffOrdersMobile will still advance the whole order when a waiter accepts one dish. FIX: replace the single `Order.create` + `OrderItem.bulkCreate` block with the required per-cart-line loop, splitting `discount_amount` proportionally, preserving `quantity`, generating a unique `public_token` per order, calling `getNextOrderNumber` once per iteration, and updating `Partner` once with the final accumulated counters.
.\pages\PublicMenu\review_2026-04-07.md:6:3. [P1] Fix 2 not implemented in pickup/delivery submit path — [`pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx`](C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx) lines 4094-4124 still build one `orderData`, call `Order.create` once, and `bulkCreate` all `OrderItem`s under that order. That leaves delivery/takeaway in the same forbidden `1 Order + N OrderItems` structure instead of `N` orders with one item each. FIX: replace this block with the specified per-cart-line loop, using shared base fields and per-item `total_amount`, `discount_amount`, and `public_token`, while keeping `order_number` and `split_type` absent.
