.\pages\PublicMenu\review_2026-04-15.md:5:1. [P0] `statusBuckets` still groups by legacy `o.status` only — In [CartView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:427), the drawer decides `served` vs `in_progress` from `o.status`, while terminal completion now comes from `Order.stage_id -> OrderStages.internal_code`. A waiter/SOM move to the `finish` stage can therefore leave the order in `В работе`, which matches the bug described in Fix 1. `getOrderStatus` in [useTableSession.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/useTableSession.jsx:797) also still returns only `{ icon, label, color }`, so CartView has no stage code to consume. FIX: extend `getOrderStatus(order)` to return `internal_code`, then make `statusBuckets` stage-first with legacy `o.status` fallback exactly as described in Fix 1.
