+Recommended three targeted changes for SOM B2.2 discovery. First, treat `openId = null` as “unknown / cache-stale” and only force a table group into `completed` on a positive mismatch between `openSessionByTableId[group.id]?.id` and `group.sessionId`; mirror that in `tabCounts`. Second, fix historical-card merging by adding closed `TableSession` ground truth and matching missing `table_session` links back to real sessions via `opened_at`/`closed_at`, keeping a synthetic key only as a last-resort fallback. Third, reuse that same matched session metadata to show `закрыт HH:mm` plus order-derived total on collapsed completed cards. Main caveat: if B44 literal-nulls `order.table_session` before `activeOrders` runs, the hall-order filter at `staffordersmobile.jsx:3598-3600` will also need a narrow relaxation for matchable historical orders.
